(277026, 9142, 276984, 'Trigger_happy78', 4053, '', 1340955011, '[QUOTE=Nazim Sahib;276984]I dont have much experience with safe action triggers but i always keep my handgun chambered and i just honestly dont feel safe with safe action systems thats my veiw im sure others would disagree.\nThis handgun is much safer due to its decocker and is something i would really consider.Just wish a member would give a going over.[/QUOTE]\n\nYour right bro. I also carry my safe-action gun chambered. I also am not 100% comfortable with that. But is TP9 with a decocker a better option then a Caracal. Nah, here is why i think that. Decocker on a external hammer gun or gun with external hammer decocked, is better because you can visually see that hammer is decocked and use DA pull to fire a round. While on a striker fired gun you can''t see/ or forget if the gun is decocked or even cocked in the first place. So there is a risk of gun going CLICK instead of BOOM in a bad place in a bad time.', 1, 0, '119.154.92.156', 0, 1, 0, 0, 0, 'on_nl2br', 0, 0),
