(282782, 9142, 275786, 'rmishaq', 6388, '', 1343228173, 'Wha!!?? My hard thought posts... Gone!!??\n\nAnyway..back to topic.\n\nRechecked the Canik today in terms of a carry. Didn''t have much time coz the people were in some sort of hurry ... God knows where they wanted to go at 6:30 in the evening ...\n\nReally nice sights and a good pointer. The trigger surprisingly does not seem very spongy for a polymer DA/SA. My experience with Taurus and to some extent even the USP was that I didn''t quite like the trigger (love the USP though). The DA pull feels a little less 10lbs. SA is nice and should be about 2.5-3.\n\nI have mixed feelings about the weight; I don''t know if anyone would understand but ... It''s a little light. I know..I know...good for CC and all but it''s just that I can''t seem to get a handle on the balance of the gun. Maybe I needed to play with it a bit more. \n\nAll in all...the TP9 is beginning to look really interesting and I am reeeeaallllyyy close to getting it. I wonder if I can get it at 55k if I don''t buy the holsters and stuff :/!?', 1, 1, '42.83.84.1', 0, 1, 0, 0, 0, 'on_nl2br', 0, 0),
